#Univariate analysis for Categorical values
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

for col in cat_cols:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    data[col].value_counts().plot(kind="bar",color="lightcoral")
    plt.title(f"bar Plot of (col)")
    plt.xlabel(col)
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.show()
In[17]:
#Univariate analysis for Numerical values
for col in num_cols:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    data[col].plot(kind = "hist",bins = 20 ,color = "lightcoral",edgecolor = "black")
    plt.title(f"Histrogram of (col)")
    plt.xlabel(col)
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.show()
